@startuml Leader Robot State Chart
title Leader Robot — State Machine\n(TurtleBot3 Burger, ROS2 Humble)

skinparam state {
    BackgroundColor LightBlue
    BorderColor DarkBlue
    ArrowColor DarkBlue
    FontSize 12
}

skinparam note {
    BackgroundColor LightYellow
    BorderColor Orange
}

[*] --> INIT : system start

state INIT {
    [*] --> waiting_sensor_ready
    waiting_sensor_ready --> ready : sensors OK\n& ROS topics active
}

INIT --> WAITING_FOR_FOLLOWER : follower READY signal\nnot yet received\n[timeout: 60s]

note right of INIT
  Entry actions:
  - Initialize ROS2 nodes
  - Start SLAM toolbox
  - Enable LiDAR
  - Publish STATUS=INIT

  Transition guard:
  - Wait for /follower/command:CMD_READY
end note

state WAITING_FOR_FOLLOWER {
    [*] --> paused_at_start
    paused_at_start --> paused_at_start : heartbeat\n(publish status every 1s)
}

WAITING_FOR_FOLLOWER --> EXPLORING : [follower_status.distance ≤ FOLLOW_THRESHOLD\n AND follower_status.state = FOLLOWING]
WAITING_FOR_FOLLOWER --> WAITING_FOR_FOLLOWER : follower approaching\n(stay paused)

note right of WAITING_FOR_FOLLOWER
  Entry actions:
  - Stop motors (cmd_vel = 0)
  - Publish STATUS=WAITING_FOR_FOLLOWER

  Invariant (Uppaal): t ≤ 60s
  After 60s without follower → ERROR state
end note

state EXPLORING {
    [*] --> navigating
    navigating --> scan_checking : LiDAR update
    scan_checking --> navigating : path clear
    scan_checking --> dead_end_check : forward blocked
    dead_end_check --> navigating : escape route found
    dead_end_check --> [*] : no escape\n→ DEAD_END
}

EXPLORING --> DEAD_END : dead end detected\n(forward ≤ 0.4m blocked,\nescape routes blocked)
EXPLORING --> WAITING_FOR_FOLLOWER : follower too far\n(distance > FAR_THRESHOLD = 1.5m)
EXPLORING --> WAITING_FOR_LOST_FOLLOWER : follower status timeout\n(no msg for > 5s)

note right of EXPLORING
  Entry actions:
  - Resume navigation
  - Resume SLAM mapping
  - Publish STATUS=EXPLORING

  Internal every 100ms:
  - Send nav2 frontier goal
  - Monitor follower distance
  - Check LiDAR for dead ends

  Dead-end detection:
  - Forward sector (±30°): all ranges < 0.4m
  - Left sector (60°-120°): all ranges < 0.4m
  - Right sector (240°-300°): all ranges < 0.4m
end note

state DEAD_END {
    [*] --> signaling
    signaling --> waiting_ack : CMD_DEAD_END sent
    waiting_ack --> waiting_ack : retry every 2s
    waiting_ack --> [*] : CMD_BACKED_UP received
}

DEAD_END --> REVERSING : follower backed up\n(CMD_BACKED_UP received)
DEAD_END --> REVERSING : timeout (15s)\nforce reversal

note right of DEAD_END
  Entry actions:
  - Stop motors
  - Send /follower/command: CMD_DEAD_END
  - Publish STATUS=DEAD_END

  Invariant (Uppaal): t ≤ 15s
  If follower does not ack in 15s:
    force transition to REVERSING
end note

state REVERSING {
    [*] --> backing_out
    backing_out --> turning : obstacle cleared
    turning --> [*] : new heading found
}

REVERSING --> EXPLORING : path cleared\n(forward sector free)\n& rotation complete
REVERSING --> WAITING_FOR_LOST_FOLLOWER : follower lost during reversal

note right of REVERSING
  Entry actions:
  - Cancel current Nav2 goal
  - Drive backward (cmd_vel.linear.x = -0.1)
  - Send /follower/command: CMD_LEAD_TEMPORARILY
  - Publish STATUS=REVERSING

  Exit actions:
  - Turn to find new path
  - Send /follower/command: CMD_RESUME
  - Publish STATUS=EXPLORING
end note

state WAITING_FOR_LOST_FOLLOWER {
    [*] --> halted
    halted --> searching_broadcast : every 2s
    searching_broadcast --> halted : no response
    searching_broadcast --> [*] : CMD_FOUND_YOU received
}

WAITING_FOR_LOST_FOLLOWER --> EXPLORING : follower found\n(CMD_FOUND_YOU received\n& distance ≤ FOLLOW_THRESHOLD)
WAITING_FOR_LOST_FOLLOWER --> WAITING_FOR_LOST_FOLLOWER : still searching\n(stay halted, broadcast I_AM_HERE)

note right of WAITING_FOR_LOST_FOLLOWER
  Entry actions:
  - Stop all motion
  - Send /follower/command: CMD_SEARCH_FOR_ME
  - Publish STATUS=WAITING_FOR_LOST_FOLLOWER

  Internal every 2s:
  - Publish /leader/command: CMD_I_AM_HERE
    with current pose in data field

  Invariant (Uppaal): t ≤ 120s
end note

' Error/terminal state
state ERROR {
}

INIT --> ERROR : sensor failure\nor ROS2 timeout
WAITING_FOR_FOLLOWER --> ERROR : timeout > 60s\n& no follower found
WAITING_FOR_LOST_FOLLOWER --> ERROR : timeout > 120s\n& follower not found

ERROR --> [*] : operator intervention

note on link
  All states: emergency_stop signal → ERROR
end note

@enduml
